The paper deals with coding over continuous channels, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The specific channel model considered is the additive exponential noise (AEN) channel, which is a type of stochastic interference channel and falls under the subfield of statistical inference (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the optimization formulation for achieving the achievable rate result, which involves solving a constrained optimization problem, and thus could be categorized under the subfield of numerical analysis and optimization (cs.NI). The paper also mentions the use of low-complexity capacity-achieving codes, which could be categorized under the subfield of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) or machine learning (cs.LG).
